Wood or hyphae is a block that has the log's "bark" texture on all six sides. It comes in 11 types: oak, spruce, birch, jungle, acacia, dark oak, mangrove, cherry, crimson, warped, and pale oak.
Wood and hyphae can be broken by hand, but using an axe is the fastest.
correct tool, drops nothing or something other than the block itself
These durations ignore other influential factors (e.g., Mining Fatigue) and are measured in seconds. For more information, see Breaking  Speed.
correct tool, drops the block itself
Acacia wood can generate in savanna villages.
Mangrove wood can generate in some entrance rooms of trial chambers.
Spruce wood can generate in snowy taiga and taiga villages.
Wood or hyphae can be crafted out of four matching logs or stems, yielding three wood or hyphae as a result.
Wood and hyphae can be placed in three orientations, similarly to normal logs.
Wood can be used as a fuel in furnaces, smelting 1.5 items per block.
Hyphae cannot be used as a fuel in furnaces.
Using an axe on wood or hyphae turns it into stripped wood or hyphae, which acts the same as regular wood or hyphae.
Cocoa beans can be placed on the side of jungle wood to grow new cocoa pods.
Wood and hyphae can be placed under note blocks to produce "bass" sounds.
